      "transliteration": "ananyāḥ",
      "type": "adjective",
      "definition": "Without other, exclusive; undivided attention. The mind not fragmented between desires. Essential for exclusive devotion (ananya-bhakti).",
      "roots": "from an- (without) + anya (other)",
      "references": ["BG 9.22"],
      "themes": ["bhakti", "concentration", "exclusive-devotion"]
    },
    {
      "term": "Paryupāsate",
      "transliteration": "paryupāsate",
      "type": "verb",
      "definition": "To serve with devotion, to worship completely. From pari (completely, around) + upāsana (sitting nearby, residing in).",
      "roots": "from pari + upāsana",
      "references": ["BG 9.22"],
      "themes": ["bhakti", "service", "worship"]
    },
    {
